# State Management Guidelines

## Provider Pattern

This project uses the Provider package for state management. Follow these patterns:

## Provider Structure

- Create providers in the `business_logic` directory of each feature
- Extend `ChangeNotifier` for state management
- Use descriptive names ending with `_provider.dart`

## Provider Registration

All providers must be registered in [main.dart](mdc:lib/main.dart) MultiProvider setup:

```dart
MultiProvider(
  providers: [
    ChangeNotifierProvider(create: (_) => YourProvider()),
    // ... other providers
  ],
  child: const MyApp(),
)
```

## State Management Best Practices

- Keep providers focused on single responsibility
- Use `notifyListeners()` to update UI when state changes
- Implement proper dispose methods for cleanup
- Use `Provider.of<ProviderType>(context)` or `context.read<ProviderType>()` to access providers

## Provider Usage in Widgets

- Use `Consumer<ProviderType>` for widgets that need to rebuild on state changes
- Use `Provider.of<ProviderType>(context, listen: false)` for one-time access
- Use `context.watch<ProviderType>()` for listening to changes

## Example Provider Structure

```dart
class ExampleProvider extends ChangeNotifier {
  // State variables
  String _data = '';

  // Getters
  String get data => _data;

  // Methods that update state
  void updateData(String newData) {
    _data = newData;
    notifyListeners();
  }

  @override
  void dispose() {
    // Cleanup resources
    super.dispose();
  }
}
```
